    'hero.description': 'I am an art director, actor and filmmaker. I live in Santiago, Chile. In addition to participating in short films and my own artistic projects, I regularly share content about interior design and architecture because I am interested in the aesthetics of spaces and objects. I am currently graduated from the Cinematography and Film and Video Production career at the ARCOS Professional Institute',
    'hero.download-cv': 'Download Resume',
    
    // Portfolio Section
    'portfolio.title': 'Elevating visual narratives',
    'portfolio.subtitle': 'Embark on a design journey that transcends pixels and takes you into the world of imagination. Explore my portfolio, where passion and creativity converge to create captivating visual narratives.',
    
    // Projects - Resúmenes para página principal
    'project.casa-hojas.title': 'The House of Leaves',
    'project.casa-hojas.description': '"The House of Leaves" is an artistic installation that explores the story of an individual whose house grows expansively and uncontrollably over time. As the years pass, the resident discovers new corridors, rooms and floors, each with remarkably distinct architectural styles.',
    
    'project.ciudad-latente.title': 'Latent City',
    'project.ciudad-latente.description': 'Through a contemplative journey we observe how the forgotten Batuco wetland is threatened by urbanization and human invasion. To portray this threat, symbolism was used, through the creation of a model that represents the capitalist city.',
    
    'project.inhumano.title': 'Inhuman',
    'project.inhumano.description': 'The "Inhuman" project is a short film that plans to show the lowest of the human being, using a visual language focused on the environment and atmosphere. For the scenery, materials, wood and paint were reused, creating a neglected and dirty environment that enhances the dystopian and noir idea.',
    
    'project.retrato-oval.title': 'Oval Portrait',
    'project.retrato-oval.description': 'A student seeks to contact the artist (Boisvert) who inspired him to dedicate himself to cinema and animation, a journey of admiration that slowly transforms into obsession. The scenery combines mr.Doodle illustrations with Boisvert works, exploring black and white aesthetics.',

    'project.kamtchatka.title': 'Kamtchatka',
    'project.kamtchatka.description': 'Gregorio, an illegal immigrant, films the suicide of a bandaged woman in the Costanera mall; his body grotesquely merges with hers and, tormented and haunted, he returns to the site to record his own leap into the void.',

    // Projects - Descripciones completas para páginas individuales
    'project.casa-hojas.full-description': '"The House of Leaves" is an artistic installation that explores the story of an individual whose house grows expansively and uncontrollably over time. As the years pass, the resident discovers new corridors, rooms and floors, each with remarkably distinct architectural styles. This narrative reflects the uncontrolled growth of a city or urbanization through the experience of this character who inhabits a strange and constantly changing space.\n\nThe installation presents five year 2000 televisions that allow the public to build their own versions of the narrative, highlighting the use of architectural contrasts. Each visual element was carefully designed to represent different eras and styles, creating an immersive experience that reflects the complexity of uncontrolled urban growth.',
    
    'project.ciudad-latente.full-description': 'Through a contemplative journey we observe how the forgotten Batuco wetland is threatened by urbanization and human invasion guided by a person who was born and raised in the town. To portray this threat, symbolism was used, through the creation of a model that will represent the capitalist city and various elements that will generate visual counterpoint.\n\nThe project combines staging and visual contrast elements to create a profound reflection on the impact of urbanization on natural ecosystems. The symbolic model confronts urban expansion with wetland preservation, using materials and textures that emphasize the tension between the natural and the artificial.',
    
    'project.inhumano.full-description': 'The "Inhuman" project is a short film that plans to show the lowest of the human being, by using a visual language focused on the environment and atmosphere it produces on the viewer. For the location, several ideas were considered, but the riskiest idea was decided upon: making the scenery, reusing materials, wood and paint.\n\nFor the setting, materials that gave poor and old textures were used, the aim was to create a neglected and dirty environment. Both the space and the characterization of the characters sought to enhance this dystopian and noir idea. The recycled scenography and noir ambiance were specifically designed to enhance the dystopian atmosphere, working with aged wood and paint textures that transmit a sense of decadence and abandonment.',
    
    'project.retrato-oval.full-description': 'An Arcos student seeks to contact the artist (Boisvert) who inspired him to dedicate himself to cinema and animation, a journey of admiration that slowly transforms into obsession as the days pass.\n\nThe scenery is decorated by illustrations by artist mr.Doodle in combination with works by Boisvert himself. The treatment is thought of in terms of the aesthetics of the image, and the importance of this world that is often presented to us in black and white. Both Boisvert\'s symbolism and Doodle\'s aesthetics deepen the story, giving it visual form and structure according to what we want to demonstrate. The decoration with Mr. Doodle illustrations and monochrome aesthetic reference explore the themes of obsession and art, creating a visual universe that reflects the protagonist\'s mental state.',
    
    'project.kamtchatka.full-description': 'In 2014, Santiago de Chile. Gregorio (32), is an illegal immigrant who enters the Costanera mall illegally at night with the intention of filming a video. Driven by his obsession, he films in complete silence as he explores the structure, entering the less illuminated corridors and stopping in front of empty stores.\n\nWhen he reaches the third floor, he discovers in the penumbra Maria (23), a disfigured woman covered in bandages, an exotic midnight dress and golden jewelry. She, as if expecting it, jumps into the void when discovered, but does not leave a corpse on the ground. Gregorio, upon returning to his room and insulted by his landlady La Mona (57), reviews the video clips and confirms that he has filmed the suicide.\n\nThe camera\'s tape behaves strangely. Gregorio experiences nausea, itching and vertigo; his body emits an unbearable odor. The constant repetition of the video clip triggers a terrifying vision of Maria. In shock, he turns off the computer and discovers a female ear on his neck. When he removes his shirt, he reveals Maria\'s face growing on his back.\n\nAfter a few hours, Gregorio\'s body has changed. His flesh is rotting and his own body of Maria is emerging from his interior, leading him to a state of despair. Deciding, dragged by horror, to amputate Maria\'s body from his own using a knife. Finally, Gregorio returns to the Costanera mall, enters the underground channels of Santiago, returns to the floor where he witnessed Maria\'s suicide, leaves the camera on the ground with the intention of recording one last video, and then jumps into the void.',
    
